[A history of men's health--on the origin of a field of research].

[Article in German]

Dinges M.

This contribution traces the conditions surrounding the emergence and 
development of a new field of research since the millennium. It primarily 
presents research initiated by the Stuttgart Institute for the History of 
Medicine: starting with the (re)discovery of sources and the setting up of 
bodies of sources for a gender-sensitive, patient-oriented history of health 
(autobiographies, diaries, correspondence) it moves to issues such as health 
lifestyles, workers' masculinity, the use of medical services, health 
experiences during particular stages of life such as childhood or youth, as well 
as prevention, healthcare, mental health and the gender gap in life expectancy. 
In conclusion the article discusses possible theoretical frameworks and 
perspectives.

